		<published>2014-11-25T15:39:08Z</published>
		<category scheme="http://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Home Page Stories" /><category scheme="http://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Publication" /><category scheme="http://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Web Design and Applications" />		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[The CSS Working Group and the SVG Working Group invite implementations of the Candidate Recommendation of Geometry Interfaces Module Level 1. This specification provides basic geometric interfaces to represent points, rectangles, quadrilaterals and transformation matrices that can be used by other modules or specifications. Learn more about the Style Activity and the Graphics Activity.]]></summary>
		<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.w3.org/blog/news/archives/4202"><![CDATA[<p>The <a href="http://www.w3.org/Style/CSS/members">CSS Working Group</a> and the <a href="http://www.w3.org/Graphics/SVG/WG/">SVG Working Group</a> invite implementations of the Candidate Recommendation of <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2014/CR-geometry-1-20141125/">Geometry Interfaces Module Level 1</a>. This specification provides basic geometric interfaces to represent points, rectangles, quadrilaterals and transformation matrices that can be used by other modules or specifications. Learn more about the <a href="http://www.w3.org/Style/">Style Activity</a> and the <a href="http://www.w3.org/Graphics/">Graphics Activity</a>.</p>
